alerts.message: Delay Notification: As of 3:55 PM CT, Southwest Chief Train 3 which departed on 8/9/25 is operating approximately 2 hours late due to weather related speed restrictions and rail congestion from significant freight train interference.

Weather Delay: As of 6:13 AM CT, Southwest Chief Train 3 which departed on 8/10/25 will be operating approximately 2 hours late due to high wind warnings temporarily affecting the movement of rail traffic in the area, making it necessary to operate at a safer reduced speed. We thank you for your patience and understanding.

Weather Delay: As of 5:08 AM PT, Southwest Chief Train 4 which departed on 8/9/25 is operating approximately 6 hours 30 minutes late due to flash flood warnings temporarily affecting the movement of rail traffic in the area, and rail congestion from freight train interference. We thank you for your patience and understanding.

Service Resumption: As of 10:05 AM CT, California Zephyr Train 5 which departed on 8/8/25 has resumed travel and is currently operating approximately 21 hours 25 minutes late. We thank you for your patience during this delay and apologize for any inconvenience this may have caused.

Weather Delay: As of 7:24 AM CT, California Zephyr Train 5 which departed on 8/9/25 is operating approximately 4 hours late due to high wind and flash flood warnings affecting the movement of rail traffic in the area, and rail congestion from freight train interference. We thank you for your patience and understanding.
Delay Notification: As of 9:21 AM PT, California Zephyr Train 6 has departed Emeryville (EMY) and is currently operating approximately 20 minutes late.

Weather Delay: As of 7:27 AM CT, Empire Builder Train 7/27 which departed Chicago on 8/10/25 is operating approximately 8 hours 50 minutes late due to a mechanical assessment conducted prior to departure, and flash flood warnings temporarily affecting the movement of rail traffic in the area making it necessary to travel at a safer reduced speed. Train 7/27 will incur an additional delay due to a mandatory crew change based on federal guidelines for hours-of-service. We thank you for your patience and understanding.
Travel Update: As of 6:27 PM PT, Train 8 departed Seattle (SEA) operating approximately 1 hour and 25 minutes late. We sincerely apologize for this delay.

Weather Delay: As of 5:21 AM CT, Train 21/421 which departed on 8/10/25 is operating approximately 2 hours late due to flash flood warnings temporarily affecting the movement of rail traffic in the area, and rail congestion from freight train interference. We thank you for your patience and understanding.

Delay Notification: As of 5:48 AM CT, Texas Eagle Train 22 will experience a delay of approximately 1 hour departing San Antonio (SAS) due to the late arrival of the inbound trainset and a late release from the maintenance facility servicing and processing the trainset in preparation for departure. We are making every effort to minimize your wait time and will provide updates to you as soon as they become available. We sincerely apologize for any inconvenience this may cause.
Travel Update: As of 8:02 PM CT, Train 41 departed Chicago (CHI), operating approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes late. We sincerely apologize for this delay.
Travel Update: As of 9:38 PM CT, Train 48 departed Chicago (CHI) operating approximately 5 minutes late. We sincerely apologize for this delay.

Travel Advisory: As of 4:36 PM ET, Your train may experience a delay due to single-tracking between Croton-Harmon NY (CRT) and Poughkeepsie NY (POU). Delays up to 1 hour may be expected traveling through the area. We sincerely apologize for the inconvenience this may cause and thank you in advance for your patience and understanding.
Delay Notification: As of 6:48 PM ET, Train 97 is operating approximately 55 minutes late due to the opening and closing of the Bush River Bridge. We sincerely apologize for this delay.
Delay Notification: As of 6:09 AM PT, Your train is currently stopped at Martinez (MTZ) due to the scheduled opening and closing of the Suisun Bay Bridge. We thank you for your patience.
